{% extends 'layout.html.twig' %}

{% block stylesheets %}
  {{ parent() }}
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ asset('build/behaviour.style.css') }}" />
{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
  {% include 'frontend/_hero.html.twig' with {
  'icon': 'bundles/app/images/homegraphic-bc.svg',
  'icon_alt': 'Behavioural Science',
  'header': 'Behavioural Science'
  } %}

  <section class="behaviour-diagram detailed" id="diagram">
    <div class="container-fluid">
      <div class="row no-gutters">
        <div class="col-md-3 text-center diagram-info">
          <img src="{{ asset('bundles/app/images/bsicon-info.svg') }}" alt="Info info - lower case 'i'" class="info-icon" />
          <p>
            This is a more in-depth version of the behavioural science diagram showing <span class="inline-block">the connections.</span>
          </p>
          <a href="{{ path('behavioural_science_explain') }}" class="btn btn-block btn-explain back">
            Back to Resources
          </a>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6 triangle">
          <div class="diagram text-center">
            <div class="layout inline-block">
              <img src="{{ asset('bundles/app/images/bs-diagramdetailed.png') }}" alt="Behavioural Science Detailed Diagram" />
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-3 text-center diagram-explain">
          {%  block back_to_diagram %}
            <div class="inline-block">
              <p>View resources via the interactive Diagram</p>
              <a href="{{ category_path('behavioural science') }}" class="btn btn-block btn-explain back">
                Back to Resources
              </a>
            </div>
          {% endblock %}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="explain-diagram">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
          <h2>About the Diagram </h2>
          <p>This diagram is a simplified representation of part of the top level of the Behaviour Change Intervention Ontology. It shows a Behaviour Change Intervention 'scenario', which consists of</p>
          <ul>
            <li>an intervention,</li>
            <li>its target behaviour(s), and</li>
            <li>factors that influence the outcome of the intervention in relation to the target behaviour.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>A scenario may be hypothetical (e.g. for modelling purposes, planned (intended), or realised (enacted, for example in an evaluation).</p>
          <p>The entities in the scenario interact as shown by the arrows in the diagram. The content and delivery of an intervention influences the target behaviour through one or more mechanisms of action. The context moderates the influence of 1) the intervention on the mechanism of action and 2) the mechanisms of action on the behaviour. Exposure moderates the influence of the intervention on the mechanisms of action and is itself influenced by the intervention and context.</p>

          <h2>Example</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><b>Behaviour:</b> Cessation of cigarette smoking for at least 6 months.</li>
            <li><b>Intervention:</b> Opportunistic brief advice on smoking cessation by a GP, lasting an average of 30 seconds.</li>
            <li><b>Context:</b> Smokers attending a routine GP surgery for a health problem in the UK.</li>
            <li><b>Exposure:</b> 80% of smokers receive the advice.</li>
            <li><b>Mechanisms:</b> Increase in desire to stop smoking and confidence in quitting leading to a quit attempt.</li>
            <li><b>Outcome:</b> 7%</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row row-diagram-explain">
        <div class="col-xs-12">
          <div class="col-md-4 col-md-offset-4 text-center diagram-explain">
            {{ block('back_to_diagram') }}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
{% endblock %}